
[1]hackle

   HACK'LE, v.t.

   1. To comb flax or hemp; to separate the coarse part of these
   substances from the fine, by drawing them through the teeth of a
   hatchel.

   2. To tear asunder.

      HACK'LE, n. A hatchel. The latter word is used in the U. States.

   1. Raw silk; any flimsy substance unspun.

   2. A fly for angling, dressed with feathers or silk.
